lenders.name: Fred Molloy
lenders.occupational_info:
Fred Molloy is a registered migration agent, with the Office of the Migration Agent Registration Authority (MARN #0853698) and a member of the Migration Institute of Australia. He also possesses an honours degree in Business Studies (Finance) from Dublin City University (DCU). He has completed the Graduate Certificate in Migration Law and Practice at Australian National University (ANU), with membership of the Golden Key National Honours Society (for academic excellence). Fred is also a member of the Recruitment Consulting Services Association (RCSA) and serves the community as a Justice of the Peace (JP). 

 Fred is originally from Ireland, having migrated to Australia over 10 years ago, and draws on these experiences to assist and guide other migrants. He is extremely ethical, works to the MARA & RCSA codes of conduct in practice, and is exceptionally thorough which assists in processing migration applications. He also draws on his diverse working experience in adding value to submissions and applications. He has established contacts overseas who will source people with required skills sets. He deals with each person as an individual and treats each person equally, thus serving Konnecting's clients with the utmost of care.
